Producers have been remixing tracks from Ono's deep catalog of avant-garde music for the past decade.

"At first I was prejudiced against the idea," she says. "I had the pride of a rocker. People can get very elitist very quickly, and that's how I was."

When she was first approached about remixing "Walking On Thin Ice" she was especially resistant because that was the song John Lennon was working on when he died.

"I was like, 'No, never! Don't change anything!'" she says. "It was a very sensitive subject for me."

